    "ideation": "The chipmunk is defined by high-frequency twitchiness and a state of perpetual alertness. The performance focuses on the rapid expansion of the cheeks and the frantic searching of the eyes. I use eye gaze asynchrony and scale shifts to simulate the 'jitter' of a small rodent. The mouth wave acts as the 'pouch'—starting narrow, then filling up into a high-frequency buzz to represent stored nuts or a chattering scold. The color palette uses warm nut-browns and bright forest-highlights to keep the character feel earthy but energetic.",
